   535	 "All the Jaguar talk on GEnie is trivial. Everone asking eachother if
   536	 they saw the commercial. How great it looks. How well it is being
   537	 marketed. Which store chain has confirmed if they are going to carry
   538	 it. There is also some people talking about having ordered one and
   539	 that some stores have already pre-sold hundreds of units. It's like a
   540	 bunch of sports fans rallying around a sports team. Talking about the
   541	 new uniforms, or the new stadium. No better, no worse. I have no
   542	 interest in such things, but I have not bothered Ignoring permanently
   543	 that CAT. Perhaps because I enjoy looking at so many happy people."
   544	
   545	
   546	 From the Atari Vendor's Forum
   547	 =============================
   548	
   549	 Rafael Hermoso asks:
   550	
   551	 "Is Neodesk 4 out yet? If not, when? If so, where can I purchase it?"
   552	
   553	 Rick Flashman of Gribnif Software tells Rafael:
   554	
   555	 "No, NeoDesk 4 is not out yet.  We've been forced to delay its
   556	 shipping until early '94.  Part of this delay was that we wanted to
   557	 insure that Geneva was as bug-free as possible and that we had
   558	 resolved any minor issued that might have arisen as of its initial
   559	 release.  We now believe this strategy has paid off, as we've been
   560	 able to correct some minor problems with Geneva (that only showed up
   561	 after shipping) and therefore we now have a substancially more solid
   562	 package."
   563	
   564	 John Brenner tells us:
   565	
   566	 "After many years I am still using INTERLINK to do any BBS'ing
   567	 outside of GEnie. I have just D/L a file on this system and did
   568	 not remember how slow XMODEM transfer was. Are there any Interlink
   569	 TXF files in the libraries that support the other protocals available
   570	 on Compuserve. And which one is most recommended?"
   571	
   572	 Jim Ness nudges John about "getting with it":
   573	
   574	 "Geez, John, with all the terrific ST terminal programs out there, you
   575	 are still using good old Interlink?  There's Flash II, STalker, and
   576	 now the shareware gem STorm...
   577	
   578	 All three of those support CIS B and ymodem-g, the two fastest
   579	 protocols."
   580	
   581	 John tells Jim:
   582	
   583	 "I used to have Flash before I got Interlink many years ago. I never
   584	 looked at Flash II since I never liked Flash to begin with. I D/L
   585	 STorm last week. I also dont' like very much the way it is set up.
   586	 I have a friend who uses STalker. He has to buy another program to
   587	 do on-line editing. So, I just don't see the need to change. I have
   588	 a capture buffer, I can edit, save paste...everything I need.
   589	 I use Alladin, you know where, and now it looks like I will use
   590	 QuickCIS to log on here. So I really don't see why I should change.
   591	 I only upgrade software that no longer suits my needs.
   592	
   593	 I was starting to think I might need something for here since I
   594	 couldn't get QuickCIS to dial, but all has now fallen into place
   595	 and I think I'll be very happy with it. Thanks for writting it.
   596	 I'll have to read the doc....there must be a fee for something
   597	 that will save me so much money! <Grin>"
