   614	 Don Thomas of Atari Corp posts:
   615	
   616	 "Every once in a while I am beginning to see messages in langauages
   617	 other than English... German, for instance. It sure would be cool if
   618	 CIS had some sort of translation process built-in... either on demand
   619	 or automatically."
   620	
   621	 Sysop BJ Gleason tells Don:
   622	
   623	 "As a person who has done a lot of work with Natural Language
   624	 Processing and such, it is a very tough, if not impossible task.  One
   625	 of the best jokes about it is:
   626	
   627	        A program translates from russian to english and back.  The
   628	        program puts in the phrase:
   629	
   630	                "The spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak."
   631	
   632	        It is translated to russian, and then the russian is fed back
   633	        and the translation comes back as:
   634	
   635	                "The wine is good but the meat is spoiled."
   636	
   637	 Back on the subject of the Jaguar again, Don Thomas tells us:
   638	
   639	 "I stopped by an Electronics Boutique this past weekend in Pleasanton,
   640	 CA (40-50 miles East of San Francisco). I pretended to be Joe Blow
   641	 consumer and observed two 3DO systems on a shelf. The salesman said
   642	 they are not selling well, BUT he would love to take my pre-order for
   643	 the Jaguar. He said he didn't know what game came with it or how many
   644	 controllers, but that he couldn't find an end to the waiting list the
   645	 store had established for the Jaguar. It felt good.
   646	
   647	 My son even said this past Friday without me asking that all the kids
   648	 at school were talking about the Jaguar (he's ten). He told me that he
   649	 felt good telling his friends that his Dad worked at Atari."
